---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="Quiet The Mowers privacy policy — how we handle your data.">

<article class="section">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="prose">

      <p><em>Last updated: April 2026</em></p>

      <h2>1. What We Collect</h2>
      <p>Quiet The Mowers is a civic-tech platform. We collect only what we need to make the platform work:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account information:</strong> Name, email address, and optional profile details when you create an account.</li>
        <li><strong>Petition signatures:</strong> Name, email, ZIP code, and optional comment when you sign a petition. Your email is never displayed publicly.</li>
        <li><strong>Measurement data:</strong> Noise readings, timestamps, locations, and optional photos/audio when you upload measurements.</li>
        <li><strong>Testimonials:</strong> Stories you choose to share, with your preferred level of attribution.</li>
        <li><strong>Rental requests:</strong> Name, shipping address, and payment information when you rent a sound meter.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To connect you with campaigns and organizers in your area</li>
        <li>To send campaign updates to petition signers (opt-out available)</li>
        <li>To aggregate anonymized noise data for regional heatmaps and advocacy</li>
        <li>To process device rentals and shipping</li>
        <li>To send the monthly newsletter (opt-in only)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We never sell your data. We never share your email address with third parties without your explicit consent.</p>

      <h2>3. Your Choices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Measurement privacy:</strong> Each measurement can be public, anonymous-public ("a user in 80303"), or private.</li>
        <li><strong>Testimonial attribution:</strong> You choose how your story is credited — full name, first name only, or anonymous.</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> Opt out of any email category at any time. Every email includes an unsubscribe link.</li>
        <li><strong>Profile visibility:</strong> Public organizer profiles are opt-in. You may remain anonymous as an organizer.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Data Retention & Deletion</h2>
      <p>We retain your data as long as your account is active or as needed to provide the platform. You may request deletion of your data at any time by contacting privacy@quietthemowers.com. Petition signatures are retained to maintain the integrity of campaign records, but personal information is removed upon request.</p>

      <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use essential cookies for authentication and session management. We use Plausible Analytics for anonymous, privacy-respecting usage statistics — no tracking cookies, no personal data collection.</p>

      <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Clerk</strong> — Authentication provider. See Clerk's privacy policy.</li>
        <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — Payment processing for device rental shipping. See Stripe's privacy policy.</li>
        <li><strong>Resend</strong> — Transactional email delivery. See Resend's privacy policy.</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — Hosting and CDN. See Cloudflare's privacy policy.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>Quiet The Mowers is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.</p>

      <h2>8. Contact</h2>
      <p>For privacy questions or data requests, contact privacy@quietthemowers.com.</p>

      <h2>9. GDPR / CCPA</h2>
      <p>We support the rights granted under GDPR and CCPA, including the right to access, correct, delete, and port your data. To exercise these rights, contact privacy@quietthemowers.com. We will respond within 30 days.</p>

    </div>
  </div>
</article>

</Layout>
